V

voteID - Variable in class lab6Elections.VoteRecorder
The voteID, can be used to figure out what voter this is, defaults to voters +1
VoteRecorder - Class in lab6Elections
Holds the names for the candidates for both president and vice-president Records the total amount of votes Allows the names for candidates to be changed, but only when the number of votes is 0 for all candidates Allows the votes to be reset.
VoteRecorder() - Constructor for class lab6Elections.VoteRecorder
Default constructor, sets voteID and increments the amount of voters
VoteRecorder(int, int) - Constructor for class lab6Elections.VoteRecorder
This constructor is used in the testing of this whole program, it records votes without any user interaction
VoteRecorder(String, String, String, String) - Constructor for class lab6Elections.VoteRecorder
This constructor does not count, it is a constructor used to only set names of the presidents The constructor sets the votes back to 0 for all of this type
voters - Static variable in class lab6Elections.VoteRecorder
Holds the amount of total voters, this is used to calculate the next voteID in case a voter does not vote for a president of vice president
votesCandidatePresident1 - Static variable in class lab6Elections.VoteRecorder
Total amount of votes that have been cast for the first candidate for president.
votesCandidatePresident2 - Static variable in class lab6Elections.VoteRecorder
Total amount of votes that have been cast for the second candidate for president.
votesCandidateVicePresident1 - Static variable in class lab6Elections.VoteRecorder
Total amount of votes that have been cast for the first candidate for vice president.
votesCandidateVicePresident2 - Static variable in class lab6Elections.VoteRecorder
Total amount of votes that have been cast for the second candidate for vice president.
